Apple today seeded a second release candidate version of <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/macos-sequoia/">macOS Sequoia</a> 15.7, one week after seeding the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/08/05/apple-seeds-macos-15-7-rc-to-developers/">first release candidate</a>. If no further bugs are found, &zwnj;macOS Sequoia&zwnj; 15.7 could be released to the public soon.<br/>
<br/>
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-955370" src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2024/06/macOS-Sequoia-Feature.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" /><br/>
Developers can opt-in to the ‌&zwnj;macOS Sequoia&zwnj;‌ beta through the Software Update section of the System Settings app.<br/>
<br/>
According to Apple's release notes, the update includes security fixes.<br/>
<blockquote>This update provides important security fixes and is recommended for all users.</blockquote><br/>
